		<p>@Otto: It is very dangerous to go by the slot numbers on the mother board to decide which disk to replace!<br />
The order of disks as the kernel sees them does not necessarily have to be the same as the mother board slots. Especially, when a disk has failed completely so that the kernel does not detect it any more, the device names are reordered.<br />
The safest way is to go by the serial number reported by smartctl as Ferry Tooth found out.</p>

